Home          Recent  Market News   MCC Financial Advisors, LLC is a fee-based registered investment advisor providing financial planning and consulting to high net worth families, business owners, not-for-profits and other successful people and organization to help them achieve their long-term goals.As a fee-based firm and being truly independent of Wall Street, we are able to provide conflict-free advice. We have access to the best-of-breed third-party investment products and are able to deliver them to clients in an unbiased, low-cost manner. Most importantly, we are a fiduciary, so our clients interests always come first.​​MCC Financial Advisors LLC is registered with the State of Indiana​   Overview    ​​MCC Financial Advisors provides independent financial consulting, planning and asset management, free of conflicts from Wall Street.​           Midwestern  Focus    ​Independent, Objective Financial Advice    HomeCompanyServicesOur ApproachManaging PrincipalContact Us      Copyright ©​ MCC Financial Advisors, LLC.  CompanyServicesContact UsManaging PrincipalOur ApproachHome  View on MobileServices  HomeCompanyServicesOur ApproachManaging PrincipalContact Us  ​Independent, Objective Financial Advice      We develop customized strategies to protect a family's security and assets.  Our approach is proactive, and we can assist with selecting a trustee, finding tax saving strategies, gifting opportunities, and methods to protect your estate or develop a succession plan. We are experienced in, and will assist with, reviewing wills and trusts, assessing retirement strategies, evaluating charitable gifting options and techniques, and analyzing estate liquidity, among other things.     Trust, Estate, Succession and Wealth Planning  We work with small companies and business owners in setting up and maintaining employee retirement plans.  We create a platform with an open architecture of investment choices that include the best of breed managers, while keeping costs low for the plan sponsor and it's participants.  We work closely with 3rd party administrators and custodians to ensure the plan is efficient and well designed. Providing regular monitoring and updates, we will help make sure everyone meets their fiduciary duty.    401(k) and retirement plan design and advisory   With an objective, independent lens, we work with clients to provide holistic investment advice and implementation.  From determining a tailored investment strategy and creating an investment policy to selecting an appropriate asset allocation and delivering the best investment product for each situation, we are capable of handling your wealth in a comprehensive manner.  This includes integrating a financial plan into a risk assessment and providing ongoing monitoring and portfolio rebalancing.   Investment Consulting & Outsourced CIO  We can simplify client situations via a collaborative approach with other service providers.  Many times clients need one firm to bring their array of relationships together to orchestrate the myriad tasks.   We are equipped to do that and have the experience to coordinate firms including banks, estate planners, attorneys, tax accountants, insurance brokers, brokerage firms and any administrative staff or family office teams. Our independence and objectivity ensure you will be receiving the best advice.   Investment Strategy and Portfolio Design,  Implementation and Monitoring  We address a wide variety of financial issues relating to the integration of investment strategy, spending, retirement planning, gifting, estate planning, philanthropy, insurance, liability management and taxes. Utilizing analytical models, we can create financial forecasts for our clients to better understand the options available to them.  Our Services    ​  Financial Planning and Forecasting    Copyright ©​ MCC Financial Advisors, LLC.  CompanyServicesContact UsManaging PrincipalOur ApproachHome    View on MobileMichael R. Broderick    With over 25 years of industry experience, Mike has worked with and advised $100+ million family offices, retired COOs of multi-billion dollar public companies, deca-million dollar foundations and not-for-profits, small business retirement plans as well as entrepreneurs, doctors and wealthy individuals and families.  Before MCC Financial Advisors, Mike was with JPMorgan Private Bank and Credit Suisse Private Banking as a Managing Director and Senior Advisor in the Midwest.  Mike also has over a decade of investment banking experience, including as a Managing Director and Group Head of Asia Pacific TMT Banking with JPMorgan in Hong Kong. Additionally, he spent time in New York CIty as a Vice President in Mergers and Aquisitions with Merrill Lynch Institutional Banking.​Prior to his finance experience, Mike spent several years in accounting with PwC in Chicago, preparing small business financial statements as well as completing personal and business tax returns. ​​  Relavent Experience  Education & Training  Mike is the Managing Principal of MCC Financial Advisors and has more than 25 years of financial industry experience, including as a Managing Director with JPMorgan in Hong Kong, China and Chicago, IL, and as a practicing CPA at PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC) in Chicago, IL.    HomeCompanyServicesOur ApproachManaging PrincipalContact Us  ​Independent, Objective Financial Advice    Managing Principal    email:  mbroderick@mccadvisors.com  Mike received his MBA in Finance from Duke University's Fuqua School of Business and BBA in Accounting from the University of Wisconsin.   Mike is a Certified Public Accountant and practiced in both tax and audit departments with PwC.  Background  ​ ​Michael R. Broderick, CPA, MBA    Copyright ©​ MCC Financial Advisors, LLC.  CompanyServicesContact UsManaging PrincipalOur ApproachHome    View on MobileContact Us  ​Independent, Objective Financial Advice       Name: *   Email: *Check here to receive email updates   Subject: *   Message: *   Thank you 