Capital Markets

Company Overview of MCC Advisors LLC



Snapshot People




Company Overview
MCC Advisors LLC is a private equity firm specializing in investments in privately negotiated debt and equity securities of privately held small and middle market companies. It targets private debt investments ranging in size from $10 million to $50 million to borrowers principally located in North America. It seeks to invest in companies with enterprise values or asset values between $25 million and $250 million. The firm structures its investments as first lien senior secured loans, second lien senior secured loans, senior secured notes, senior subordinated notes, unitranche loans, and seeks warrants or other equity participation. The firm may take a board seat on its investee companies an...
MCC Advisors LLC is a private equity firm specializing in investments in privately negotiated debt and equity securities of privately held small and middle market companies. It targets private debt investments ranging in size from $10 million to $50 million to borrowers principally located in North America. It seeks to invest in companies with enterprise values or asset values between $25 million and $250 million. The firm structures its investments as first lien senior secured loans, second lien senior secured loans, senior secured notes, senior subordinated notes, unitranche loans, and seeks warrants or other equity participation. The firm may take a board seat on its investee companies and exits its investments between three years and seven years. It also provides advisory services to pooled investment vehicles, business development companies, insurance companies, and investment companies. The firm conducts in-house research to make its investments. MCC Advisors LLC was formed on April 23, 2010 and is based in New York, New York with an additional office in San Francisco, California.
Detailed Description


