Capital Markets

Company Overview of MCC Capital Partners, LLC



Snapshot People




Company Overview
MCC Capital Partners, LLC is a private equity firm specializing in family succession, management-led buyout, management buy-in, industry consolidation, corporate carve-outs, growth equity, and owner recapitalization in growing micro and middle market companies. The firm may engage in larger transactions in collaboration with its investment partners, and will also consider smaller investments as add-on or tuck-in transactions. It prefers to invest in consumer products, value-added distribution, leisure and recreation, technology and technology-enabled services, business and financial services, and specialty manufacturing sectors. The firm prefers to invest in branded consumer products compani...
MCC Capital Partners, LLC is a private equity firm specializing in family succession, management-led buyout, management buy-in, industry consolidation, corporate carve-outs, growth equity, and owner recapitalization in growing micro and middle market companies. The firm may engage in larger transactions in collaboration with its investment partners, and will also consider smaller investments as add-on or tuck-in transactions. It prefers to invest in consumer products, value-added distribution, leisure and recreation, technology and technology-enabled services, business and financial services, and specialty manufacturing sectors. The firm prefers to invest in branded consumer products companies in North America. It prefers to invest up to $50 million of equity in each transaction in companies having enterprise values of up to $100 million; EBITDA between $3 million and $15 million; and revenue between $15 million and $100 million. The firm prefers to take a controlling stake in its portfolio companies. MCC Capital Partners, LLC is based in Greenwich, Connecticut.
Detailed Description


